<div classname="{styles.pvlRoot}">
	<div class="p-6 rounded-5 bg-light mb-18" data-zesty-id="design:columns:1 column - 1 row my-3:36:88">
<div class="col-lg-12 col-md-12 col-sm-12" data-zesty-id="design:columns:1 column - 1 row my-3:36:88-1:1 column - 1 row:0">
<div class="py-5" data-zesty-id="design:design:whitespace-xl:35:98"></div>
<h5 data-zesty-id="content:text:1:76">About Project FIGHT</h5>
<div class="my-4" data-zesty-id="design:design:whitespace-md:2:36"></div>
<img src="https://s3.amazonaws.com/uss-cache.salvationarmy.org/149e12e8-9a5a-47a5-84a8-efe677045052_Project+Fight+Logo_cropped.png" alt="placeholder" class="img-fluid d-block my-3" style="max-width:100%;height:auto;" loading="lazy" data-zesty-id="content:images:2:94">
<div class="my-2" data-zesty-id="design:design:whitespace-sm:4:26"></div>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:5:71">
	North Carolina ranks&nbsp;among the top 10 states for human trafficking. In 2023, the National Human Trafficking Hotline identified nearly 400 victims of trafficking in North Carolina. That figure is likely much higher because trafficking is a hidden crime. The Salvation Army is committed to increasing community awareness, education and assistance for victims.
</p>
<p data-zesty-id="content:wysiwyg_basic:6:48">
	<span style="color:#ed1c2b;"><strong>If you&nbsp;or someone you know is the victim of trafficking, call our dedicated hotline: <a href="tel:9193906731">919-390-6731</a> or email us at <a href="mailto:NSCProject.FIGHT@uss.salvationarmy.org">NSCProject.FIGHT@uss.salvationarmy.org</a>.</strong></span>
</p>
<div class="my-2" data-zesty-id="design:design:whitespace-sm:7:30"></div>
<p data-zesty-id="content:textarea:8:20">
	Learn more about Project FIGHT from program manager Amber Moss who was featured on the CW22 program Community Matters:
</p>
<div style="display:flex" class="row d-flex" data-zesty-id="design:columns:1 Column:10:95">
<div class="column col-lg-10 col-md-12 col-sm-12 m-auto mt-3 ratio ratio-16x9" data-zesty-id="design:columns:1 Column:10:95-1:1 Column:0">
<iframe src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/nv0pODfsUBw" title="YouTube video player" allowfullscreen="" loading="lazy" class="w-100 h-100" data-zesty-id="content:embed:9:84"></iframe>
				</div>
			</div>
<div class="py-5" data-zesty-id="design:design:whitespace-xl:11:81"></div>
<div class="row g-3 my-3 align-items-stretch" data-zesty-id="design:columns:3 Columns:19:61">
<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-12 col-sm-12 d-flex flex-column" data-zesty-id="design:columns:3 Columns:19:61-1:3 Columns:0">
<div class="card-wysiwyg-body d-flex flex-column h-100 w-100 flex-fill rounded p-6 gap-3 bg-light text-dark card-outline border border-secondary-subtle" data-zesty-id="content:wysiwyg_basic:13:26"><h5>Case Management</h5>

<p>
	Project FIGHT provides crisis intervention and comprehensive case management for victims of human trafficking in North Carolina. Case managers connect victims to resources such as:
</p>

<ul>
	<li>Food, shelter and clothing</li>
	<li>Safety planning</li>
	<li>Medical care, mental health and dental services</li>
	<li>Identification, documentation, education, employment and housing</li>
	<li>Immigration/legal assistance and ESL</li>
</ul></div>
				</div>
<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-12 col-sm-12 d-flex flex-column" data-zesty-id="design:columns:3 Columns:19:61-1:3 Columns:1">
<div class="card-wysiwyg-body d-flex flex-column h-100 w-100 flex-fill rounded p-6 gap-3 bg-primary-200 text-light" data-zesty-id="content:wysiwyg_basic:15:28"><h5>Outreach and Awareness</h5>

<p>
	Project FIGHT has trained and educated over 4,500 professionals and community members on the issue of human trafficking and how individuals in our area can help combat it. We also participate in community events and reach out to vulnerable populations.&nbsp;
</p></div>
				</div>
<div class="col-lg-4 col-md-12 col-sm-12 d-flex flex-column" data-zesty-id="design:columns:3 Columns:19:61-1:3 Columns:2">
<div class="card-wysiwyg-body d-flex flex-column h-100 w-100 flex-fill rounded p-6 gap-3 bg-secondary-200 text-light" data-zesty-id="content:wysiwyg_basic:17:46"><h5>Collaboration</h5>

<p>
	Project FIGHT leads and participates in North Carolina's rapid response teams&nbsp;and&nbsp;collaborative victim centered emergency response teams. We also collaborate with state and local coalitions and work groups.&nbsp;&nbsp;
</p></div>
				</div>
			</div>
